The Prospectors & Developers Association of Canada (PDAC), one of the world’s premier mineral exploration and mining events will host an entirely virtual event in 2021 – for the first time in its 89-year history. As the COVID-19 pandemic continues to affect travel and major gatherings, the organisation recognises that staying connected is more important than ever for members, exhibitors, sponsors, attendees and numerous partners. View the preliminary programme The decision to move forward with a virtual event offers a safe and innovative solution for the industry to access its programming, investment and networking opportunities. Watch a video highlighting PDAC 2021 features and info The Convention will take place around its original dates of 7-10 March. Exact dates will be confirmed in the coming weeks and further updates will be provided as they become available. Organizers are excited to welcome you to the PDAC 2021 Convention in a new virtual setting. PDAC has been known to attract more than 25 000 people from 135 countries in recent years.